<br>
<br>
350,000 HP with 32K HP regeneration.  Fully susceptible to DoTs and nukes after he is *fully* debuffed.  He should rampage with no range limitations (i.e., if you get on the rampage list, you *will* get hit).  He should be fully hasted, and quad for about 2500 total.  He should proc &quot;Vindication of Zek&quot;, which should be a 95% aggro reducer, 5000 point dot over 10 ticks, and 2K unresistable DD.  He should also have a very special AoE - put it on a two minute timer.  When it goes off, it should make everyone within 100 - 150 feet spin for a few ticks.  During this time, he *should not* focus on the main tank.  Instead, go either to the rampage aggro list or skip down a bit on the main hate list.  Basically, the goal should be to have him concentrate on people who are *helping the warrior stay alive*.  In other words, every two minutes, RZ chews up a few clerics, casters, and other support people.  He should have warrior characteristics - flurry, enrage, bash, kick.  Should not be slowable.<br>
<br>
<br>
Why is this good?  Well, he'll do a lot of damage - and he won't just focus on the main tank.  It'll make people have very high sustained DPS, and it will make many classes necessary.  His insane regen means that you'll have to have necros and shamans.  His high HP count means you'll need mages and wizards.  He'll need to be debuffed - bards, enchanters.  Your melees will need to be healed, and not just by clerics.  When he goes after your clerics every 2 minutes, you'll need someone healing the clerics (druids, shamans).<br>
<br>
All the melees will need high damage output.  You'll need warriors for /meatshield so that your main tank lives through the dot / dd proc.<br>
<br>
I'm toying with the idea of a directed spell that is a 500% aggro increaser - obviously directed to someone other than the MT.  The goal is to have him chew someone else up - if you start getting mobs that don't focus on the MT, it will force you to invent new strategies and tactics to take him down.<br>
 <p>-- Ruba da Ogre<br>
