The only thing I think about people' suggestions here... who really wants RZ to just have insane AC/HP/DPS with your typical boss mob specials? Is that any different from thousands of other battles, other than having to be a large chunk more uber? Boring <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :\ --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/ohwell.gif ALT=":\"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Part of the art of war is strategy, tactics, and the element of surprise. While I don't think that VI will be willing to put in the work to have him bow kite and axe kite to take out casters while keeping a good run ahead of the melee (hey it's what I'd do), and I don't think he'll use terrain to his advantage, I'm sure there's a number of things they can do playing with aggro and ranges and percentages and all to leave his foes confounded.<br>
